parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on and stays on
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle slides or wheels lock up when applying the brakes
the vehicle fails to stop promptly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sliding door can cause the door to come off its track, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially when the vehicle is in motion. Additionally, it can compromise the safety of passengers and hinder the ability to close the door.
symptoms: The sliding door comes off its track
the door becomes stuck or difficult to open/close
the door falls off while loading/unloading
the door is unable to close properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat mounting can cause the seat to rock back and forth, potentially leading to accidents or injuries due to loss of control or distraction.
symptoms: The power driver seat rocks back and forth when the vehicle accelerates quickly
the seat feels unstable or loose
the seat mounting bolt/nut combo lifts off the mounting platform
the seat platform corners break off
adjacent metal around the bolt holes becomes disfigured
